
import java.util.Arrays;
class main{
    public static String palindrome(String a){
           int [] s= {2,6,4,8,7};
        int [] b= new int[s.length];
        int j=0;
        int i;
        for(i=s.length-1; i>=0; i--){
            b[j]=s[i];
            j++;
        }
            if(Arrays.equals(s,b)){
                return a;
            }
            else{
            return "not palindrome";
        }
        }

        public static void main(String[] args){
          String a= "palindrome";
            String result= palindrome(a);
            System.out.println(result);
        }
    }
First  i take one input array and create one array assigninga pointer for that empt array my index i is starts at last element of array then for eachb iteration it will be decrementing i using the pointer for 
updating the values in the new array. and i assigning the each  index value of my input array to each index value of new array and then i  check  the value of the input array is equal to the new array if is condition true it 
the palindrome or else it print not palindrome 
